  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Assistant Electronics Engineer",
  "description": "<h3>Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Assist in designing and modifying electronic circuits and control systems for gate automation and electronic locks.</p></li><li><p>Install, wire, configure, and commission electronic door and gate locking systems.</p></li><li><p>Program and configure controllers, access control units, sensors, keypads, RFID readers, and remote control systems.</p></li><li><p>Perform system testing, fault diagnosis, and troubleshooting of electronic and electromechanical components.</p></li><li><p>Carry out preventive maintenance and corrective repairs on installed systems.</p></li><li><p>Prepare wiring diagrams, technical documentation, test reports, and service records.</p></li><li><p>Support integration of access control systems with motors, relays, power supplies, and safety devices.</p></li><li><p>Ensure installations comply with electrical safety standards and technical specifications.</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>2-3 years of experience in electronics, access control, or automation systems.</p></li><li><p>Working knowledge of electronic circuits, sensors, relays, controllers, and SMPS.</p></li><li><p>Ability to read and interpret wiring diagrams and schematics.</p></li><li><p>Basic experience with PLCs or microcontrollers is an advantage.</p></li><li><p>Hands on skills with electronic test equipment</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with gate automation systems and electronic locks</p></li></ul>",
